<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="but-adv">but <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /bət; bʌt/    美 /bət; bʌt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-only">1.★ <strong>仅仅；只 (only)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is but a child.
他只是个孩子。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He left but an hour ago.
他一小时前才离去。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="but-for">but for</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[接名词，谓语动词常用虚拟语气] 倘没有；若不是：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>But for your help, I could not have succeeded.
如果没有你的帮助，我不可能成功。</p></div>

<h3 id="but-then-again">but then (again)</h3>
<p>1.<strong>不过；另一方面：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She speaks very good English. But then she did live in London for two years.
她英语讲得很好，不过她毕竟在伦敦生活过两年。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Many of the things we now benefit from would not be around <strong><em>_</em></strong> Thomas Edison.   （2015 江苏）<br />
A.thanks to<br />
B.regardless of<br />
C.aside from<br />
D.but for  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. D  </p></div>